{"article_id":"ABlmiwYo8wDE2kMy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A federal grand jury indicted former House Speaker J. Dennis Hastert Thursday with trying to circumvent currency rules","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"and then lying to the FBI","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to hide payments","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"he was making","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"for past \" misconduct \" against an individual","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"he seemingly knew from his time as a high school coach and teacher .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"The indictment doesn ' t describe his misconduct ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"but paints a stark picture of the cover-up ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"Mr. Hastert agreed to pay $ 3.5 million","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"to \" compensate for and conceal \" his past behavior against someone","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"identified in the document as \" Individual A , \"","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"who","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"the indictment suggests","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"knew Mr. Hastert most of his life .","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"Beginning in 2010 ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Mr. Hastert , 73 , and the man","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"he was paying off","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"would meet at prearranged times and locations every six weeks ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"and the former speaker would turn over $ 50,000 each time .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Federal investigators got involved","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"when Mr. Hastert ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"after being questioned by his bank about the large withdrawals ,","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"began making smaller withdrawals of less than $ 10,000 ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"then bundling them","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"to make his payments .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Federal currency transparency laws require all transactions of at least $ 10,000 to be reported to authorities ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"and breaking up withdrawals into smaller amounts is banned .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"When questioned in December about the withdrawals ,","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"Mr. Hastert lied to FBI investigators","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"by saying","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"he was keeping the cash ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"the indictment charges .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"\" From 2010 to 2014 , Hastert withdrew a total of approximately $ 1.7 million in cash from various bank accounts","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"and provided it to Individual A .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Beginning in approximately July 2012 ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Hastert started structuring his cash withdrawals in increments of less than $ 10,000","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"to evade the filing of Currency Transaction Reports , \"","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"U.S. Attorney Zachary T. Fardon ' s office said in a statement","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"announcing the indictment ,","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"handed up from a grand jury in Chicago .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"The case was pursued by the FBI and the IRS ' criminal investigation division .","depth":3},{"id":42,"text":"Mr. Hastert served two decades in the House","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"and was speaker from 1999 through 2007 ,","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"notching the longest tenure of any Republican speaker in history .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"He stepped down","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"after overseeing a disastrous election for House Republicans in 2006 ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"and led the lobbying arm of Dickstein Shapiro LLP , a Washington law firm ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"until he resigned on Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"according to a spokesman .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"Mr. Hastert didn ' t respond to an email request for comment Thursday evening .","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"He has a public policy center","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"named for him","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"at Wheaton College in Illinois ,","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"and served on several corporate boards .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"CME Group announced Thursday","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"that he had stepped down from its board ,","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"according to news reports .","depth":5},{"id":58,"text":"According to the indictment ,","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"Mr. Hastert has turned over about $ 1.7 million of the $ 3.5 million","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"he had agreed to pay to Individual A .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Of that , $ 952,000 was taken out in increments of less than $ 10,000 ,","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"which","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"investigators said","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"was done in violation of the currency law .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"When the FBI questioned Mr. Hastert ,","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"they asked","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"if he was keeping the money","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"because he didn ' t feel safe with it in the banks .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"\" Yeah ... I kept the cash .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"That ' s what I ' m doing , \"","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"he told them ,","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"according to the indictment .","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"Mr. Hastert was a high school teacher and wrestling coach in Yorkville , Illinois , from 1967 to 1981 ,","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"and the indictment says","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"Individual A is a resident of the same town","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"and \" has known defendant John Dennis Hastert most of Individual A ' s life . \"","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"The indictment says","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"the two met repeatedly in 2010 ,","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"and during one of those meetings , \" discussed past misconduct by defendant against Individual A","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"that had occurred years earlier . \"","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"During his time as House speaker , Mr. Hastert served with former Rep. Tom DeLay ,","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"who had to step down","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"after he was indicted on charges","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"of conspiring to launder campaign contributions .","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"Mr. DeLay was found guilty by a jury ,","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"but an appeals court later ruled","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"the evidence was insufficient","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"and dismissed the case .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":177,"left":146,"right":176,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":130,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":129,"right":41,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":116,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":94,"right":115,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":0,"right":93,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":1,"right":92,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":90,"right":91,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":90,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":107,"right":114,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":102,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":95,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":101,"left":8,"right":100,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":9,"right":99,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":96,"right":98,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":97,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":97,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"